{
    "word": "Very night signals",
    "definitions": [
        "A system of signaling in which balls of red and green fire are fired from a pistol, the arrangement in groups denoting numbers having a code significance. The pistol used to fire the signal flare is called a Very pistol."
    ],
    "examples": [
    ],
    "etymology": "[After Lieut. Samuel W. Very, who invented the system in 1877.]"
}